# Admin Dashboard — Core Standards

## Project Context
Personal productivity tracker built with React + TypeScript + Vite + Supabase.
Tracks: daily tasks, habits (21-day), expenses, exercise logs, office tasks.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is on — no `any` types ever
- All shared types live in `src/types.ts` — add new ones there
- Dates are always `YYYY-MM-DD` strings; use the `today()` helper from `src/store.ts`
- Use the `generateId()` helper from `src/store.ts` for new record IDs

## General Code Style
- Functional components only — no class components
- No `console.log()` in components; use `console.error()` only in catch blocks
- Keep components focused — extract logic to `store.ts`, not inline in components
- Currency is Indian Rupee: format with `toLocaleString("en-IN")` and `₹` prefix
- Monthly budget constant is `MONTHLY_BUDGET` from `src/data.ts`
